1. *Probudila* sam se u pet ujutru jer sam imala važan sastanak. (I *woke up* at 5am because I had an important meeting.)
2. Ujutru me uvek *probudi* zvuk ptica koje pevaju. (In the morning, the sound of singing birds *wakes me up*.)
3. Molim vas da ne *probudite* bebu koja spava u sobi pored. (Please don't *wake up* the baby who is sleeping in the room next door.)
4. Nisam mogao *da se probudim* iz sna jer sam bio jako umoran. (I couldn't *wake up* from my sleep because I was very tired.)
5. *Probudio* sam se kasno danas jer sam sinoć dugo radio. (I *woke up* late today because I worked late last night.)
6. Šta ako *se probudim* jednog dana i ne prepoznam svoj život? (What if I *wake up* one day and don't recognize my life?)
7. *Probudiću* te ujutru u 7 sati da bi smo stigli na vreme. (I will *wake you up* tomorrow at 7am so we can arrive on time.)
8. Bilo je tako hladno da me je samo *probudila* hladnoća. (It was so cold that the cold *woke me up*.)
9. Uvek me *probudi* šolja kafe koju mi donese moj suprug. (My husband always *wakes me up* with a cup of coffee.)
10. Nadam se da će me ova nova knjiga *probuditi* i motivisati. (I hope this new book will *awaken* and motivate me.)